    "notes": {
        "CN10_25": "PE2 is connected to both CN9 pin 14 (SAI_A_MCLK) and CN10 pin 25 (QSPI_BK1_IO2). Only one function must be used at one time.",
        "CN11_13": "PA13 and PA14 are shared with SWD signals connected to STLINK-V3E. ST does not recommend using them as I/O pins.\u00e2\u20ac\u0192",
        "CN11_15": "PA13 and PA14 are shared with SWD signals connected to STLINK-V3E. ST does not recommend using them as I/O pins.\u00e2\u20ac\u0192",
        "CN11_7": "The default state of BOOT0 is 0. It can be set to 1 when a jumper is plugged into CN11 [5-7].",
        "CN12_8": "5V_USB_STLK is the 5 V power coming from the ST-LINKV3 USB connector that rises before and it rises before the +5 V rising on the board.",
        "CN7_14": "PA7 is used as D11 and connected to CN7 pin 14. If SB31 is ON, it is also connected to Ethernet PHY as RMII_CRS_DV. In this case, only one function of the Ethernet or D11 must be used.",
        "CN7_5": "PB13 is used as I2S_A_CK and connected to CN7 pin 5. If JP6 is ON, it is also connected to Ethernet PHY as RMII_TXD1. In this case, only one function of the Ethernet or I2S_A must be used.",
        "CN9_14": "PE2 is connected to both CN9 pin 14 (SAI_A_MCLK) and CN10 pin 25 (QSPI_BK1_IO2). Only one function must be used at one time."
